# Obsidian Nexus (Primus) — Testnet Deployment Guide

A complete, step-by-step walkthrough for standing up a Primus testnet from scratch — from renting a server to your first friend sending a transaction.

> **Note:** `primus-client` is a separate, stripped-down binary meant for end users of the network/wallet — distinct from `primus-cli`, the full administrative/terminal tool covered in the rest of this repo's docs (README/SPECIFICATION/NETWORK). If `primus-client` isn't yet a workspace member in `Cargo.toml`, add it there before following Part 2.

---

### PART 1: Deploying the Network on a VPS (Ubuntu)

Connect to your server over SSH and run the following in order.

**1. Prepare the server**

Install the required system packages:
```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y curl build-essential git pkg-config libssl-dev protobuf-compiler
```

**2. Install Rust**
```bash
curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh
# Press Enter when prompted (choose the default option 1)
source "$HOME/.cargo/env"
```

**3. Upload your code**

Copy the `primus-project` folder to the server (e.g. clone it from GitHub, or transfer it via SFTP/SCP).
Enter the project directory:
```bash
cd primus-project
```

**4. Clear old data (important!)**

To make sure the Genesis block is created correctly, verify there's no leftover database from a previous run:
```bash
rm -rf .primus_db
```

**5. Build the core node**

Build the optimized release binary:
```bash
cargo build --release -p primus-core
```
*(This takes a couple of minutes.)*

**6. First run (genesis and key generation)**

Start the core node:
```bash
./target/release/primus-core --port 9000
```
The setup wizard will ask you three questions:
1. `Is this node a public SEED NODE? [y/N]` — enter **y**
2. `Detecting your public IP... Use this IP? [Y/n]` — enter **y** (if it correctly detected your server's IP)
3. `Add seed peer:` — leave blank, just press **Enter**.

> **What happens next:**
> The console will print `✅ Genesis successful! Crystal #0 created`.
> The network is now officially live. Two files are created on disk: `master.wallet` (the Architect's wallet, holding 1 billion mass) and `operator.wallet`. **Write down the mnemonic phrases** the console prints — they will not be shown again!

Stop the node with `Ctrl+C`. We'll run it in the background instead so it stays up permanently.

**7. Run the node in the background (systemd)**

Copy this whole block into the console and press Enter:
```bash
sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/primus.service > /dev/null <<EOF
[Unit]
Description=Primus Core Node
After=network.target

[Service]
User=$USER
WorkingDirectory=$PWD
ExecStart=$PWD/target/release/primus-core --port 9000
Restart=always
RestartSec=3
LimitNOFILE=65535

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
EOF
```

Enable and start the service:
```bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable primus
sudo systemctl start primus
```
*(To tail the server logs in real time: `journalctl -u primus -f`)*

